  build_analytics_mission_type:
    proposal_name: build_analytics_mission_type
    model: tencent/hy3:free
    objective: 'Build the new "analytics" mission type and the new "ANALYTICS" evolution mode. The analytics mission type is like the evolution DEEP mission but it only ANALYSES and produces analytics (findings/insights), not implementable evolution cases. The ANALYTICS evolution mode works like the RESEARCH mode but uses an analytics-based approach instead of a research-based approach. NOTE: the exact "how to think when analysing" framing will be supplied by the user later — do NOT invent the analysis methodology; scaffold the structure and wait for the user''s direction.'
    priority: MEDIUM
    state:
      class: PLANNING
      progress: pending
    rounds: 0
    goals:
      analytics_mission_type: 'Define the new "analytics" mission type: template, schema section, and a worked example mission that mirrors evolution DEEP but emits analytics findings instead of cases (no solution/how/targets — insight + evidence + metric instead).'
      analytics_evolution_mode: Add a new "ANALYTICS" evolution mode alongside FAST/DEEP/RESEARCH/INBOX, modeled on how RESEARCH works but driven by an analytics approach rather than research.
      user_analysis_framing: Hold for the user's later instruction on how the analysis should think before finalizing the analytics mission template / os_prompt.
    tasks:
      scaffold_analytics_type:
        progress: pending
        owner: agent
        detail: Add the analytics mission type to the missions template and schema, plus a starter example mission, pending the user's analysis framing.
      add_analytics_evolution_mode:
        progress: pending
        owner: agent
        detail: Register ANALYTICS as a 5th evolution mode (config + schema + daemon/frontend routing) mirroring the RESEARCH mode's shape.
      await_user_framing:
        progress: pending
        owner: user
        detail: Wait for the user to dictate how analytics missions should think when analysing, then finalize the template and os_prompt.
  restructure_toolboxes_lean:
    proposal_name: restructure_toolboxes_lean
    model: tencent/hy3:free
    objective: 'Restructure _os/os-toolboxes.yaml down to ONLY the three needed toolboxes: notebooklm, research, and a brand-new analytics toolbox. Remove every other toolbox and domain (the agentic extras - analysis, benchmarking, brainstorming, communication, documentation, evaluation, planning, rag, synthesis, validation - and the empty business domain). Then design and add new agents + skills under the three kept toolboxes. The specific new agents/skills are defined during execution - scaffold the structure and confirm the list with the user first, do not invent them.'
    priority: MEDIUM
    state:
      class: PLANNING
      progress: pending
    rounds: 0
    goals:
      keep_three_toolboxes: Collapse the toolbox tree to exactly notebooklm, research, and a new analytics toolbox; delete all other toolboxes/domains so the tree is lean.
      analytics_toolbox: Define the new analytics toolbox (description + when_to_use) modeled on the analytics mission concept - analysis that produces insights/metrics, not implementable cases.
      new_agents: Add new agents under the kept toolboxes (notebooklm, research, analytics) to cover their real workloads.
      new_skills: Add new skills under the kept toolboxes so the work is reproducible.
    tasks:
      prune_toolboxes:
        progress: pending
        owner: agent
        detail: Remove all non-kept toolboxes/domains from os-toolboxes.yaml, leaving only notebooklm, research, and a placeholder analytics toolbox.
      define_analytics_toolbox:
        progress: pending
        owner: agent
        detail: Fill in the analytics toolbox description + when_to_use; align with the analytics mission type framing (await the user's analysis-thinking input).
      design_agents:
        progress: pending
        owner: user
        detail: Agree the new agent list with the user before creating them under the three kept toolboxes.
      design_skills:
        progress: pending
        owner: user
        detail: Agree the new skill list with the user before creating them under the three kept toolboxes.
  enhance_dashboard_uiux:
    proposal_name: enhance_dashboard_uiux
    model: tencent/hy3:free
    objective: Enhance the PlugBoot dashboard (.infra/frontend) using UI/UX skills and best practices - improve layout, information hierarchy, visual clarity, interaction flow, and responsiveness across the mission/board/toolbox/ inbox views. Audit the current UI first, then propose and apply concrete UI/UX improvements. The specific improvements are defined during execution - audit first and confirm the change list with the user before applying.
    priority: MEDIUM
    state:
      class: PLANNING
      progress: pending
    rounds: 0
    goals:
      audit_ui: Audit the current dashboard UI/UX - list friction points, weak hierarchy, and inconsistent patterns across views.
      apply_uiux_skills: Apply UI/UX skills/best practices to redesign the weak areas (layout, clarity, flow, responsiveness).
      verify_changes: Confirm the changes render correctly and do not break existing mission/board/toolbox/inbox functionality.
    tasks:
      audit_dashboard:
        progress: pending
        owner: agent
        detail: Review .infra/frontend (app.js + index.html) views and list concrete UI/UX issues with severity.
      propose_changes:
        progress: pending
        owner: user
        detail: Present the proposed UI/UX change list to the user for approval before applying any edits.
      apply_enhancements:
        progress: pending
        owner: agent
        detail: Implement the approved UI/UX improvements in the frontend.
      regression_check:
        progress: pending
        owner: agent
        detail: Verify dashboard still loads and all views function after changes.
  audit_topright_entity_switcher:
    proposal_name: audit_topright_entity_switcher
    model: tencent/hy3:free
    objective: 'Investigate the dashboard''s top-right switcher (os/entity switcher). Verify (1) it correctly switches between os and each entity, and (2) when an entity is switched, ALL entity-bound fields and metrics are also switched/ re-rendered from the newly selected entity''s files. Confirm the rule: only the top-LEFT 3 items must stay constant across entity changes; everything else (all fields, metrics, mission/board/toolbox/inbox views) must follow the switched entity. Report findings: is the switcher working correctly, and where does it leak (stale fields/metrics from the previous entity, or wrong items changing).'
    priority: MEDIUM
    state:
      class: PLANNING
      progress: pending
    rounds: 0
    goals:
      trace_switcher_logic: Find and read the switcher handler (e.g. switchEntity) in the frontend and map what state it reloads on switch.
      verify_entity_switch: Confirm os<->entity and entity<->entity switching actually loads the right files (runtime, missions, toolboxes, inbox, board).
      verify_top_left_pinned: Identify the top-left 3 items and confirm they do NOT change when the entity changes.
      find_leaks: Find any field/metric/view that fails to switch or wrongly stays/leaks across entity change; list concrete bugs.
    tasks:
      read_switcher_code:
        progress: pending
        owner: agent
        detail: Read the switcher + switchEntity implementation in .infra/frontend to map reloaded state.
      run_switch_checks:
        progress: pending
        owner: agent
        detail: Walk through each switch path (os->entity, entity->entity) and note which fields/metrics re-render vs stay stale.
      report_findings:
        progress: pending
        owner: agent
        detail: 'Summarize: is the switcher correct, which items are pinned (top-left 3), and list any leakage/missing-switch bugs with fix pointers.'
